text: Jaclyn Nesheiwat Stapp (born July 29, 1980) is an American fashion model, writer and philanthropist. She was Mrs. Florida America in 2008 and Miss New York USA in 2004. In 2010, she wrote a children's book, Wacky Jacky: The True Story of an Unlikely Beauty Queen. She is the director of The Scott Stapp With Arms Wide Open Foundation and founder of CHARM which helps children from poor neighborhoods get an education. Nesheiwat is married to Creed lead singer Scott Stapp. She is the sister of Julia Nesheiwat and Janette Nesheiwat."Dr. Janette Nesheiwat." Fox News.
